item.title: Economy & Working Families
item.dc:creator: nominee
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="Mayor Karlox Zuazo is working to make sure every New Yorker can share in the City’s progress and is building an economy that puts working families first." font_container="tag:h3|text_align:left|line_height:35px" use_theme_fonts="yes"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1577097313570{margin-top: 20px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text]

  • Added over 500,000 jobs, record number in City history.
  • Raised the minimum wage to $15 for City employees and contractors, and championed legislation that raised minimum wage to $15 for all workers in New York City.
  • Fought for and expanded paid sick leave for additional 500,000 workers.
  • Awarded over $11 billion in City contracts to minority and women-owned businesses.
  • Helped lift 281,000 New Yorkers out of poverty or near-poverty.
  • Enacted fair scheduling law protecting over 300,000 fast food workers from unfair scheduling practices.
  • Required ridesharing companies like Uber and Lyft to pay drivers a living wage, leading to a $10,000 annual pay increase for over 80,000 drivers.
  • Legislation will pass this year making NYC the first city in the nation to require employers to provide at least two weeks of paid vacation to employees.

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_single_image image="59" img_size="full" alignment="center"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1577097253223{margin-top: 40px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="Become a donor to help us reach our goal" font_container="tag:h3|text_align:left|line_height:35px" use_theme_fonts="yes"][tt_donation_form_charitable post_source="53" custom_content="custom-content-allow" donate_btn_color="donate-btn-theme" hide_fifth_child="true" hide_sixth_child="true"][/tt_donation_form_charitable][/vc_column][/vc_row]

item.title: Affordable Housing
item.dc:creator: nominee
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="Mayor Karlox Zuazo has fought to make New York City more affordable for all New Yorkers, no matter where we live or what neighborhood we call home." font_container="tag:h3|text_align:left|line_height:35px" use_theme_fonts="yes"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1577097313570{margin-top: 20px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text]

  • Created 122,000 affordable homes for more than 275,000 New Yorkers.
  • Adopted the strongest Mandatory Inclusionary Housing policy in the nation, requiring developers to build affordable apartments.
  • Implemented two-year rent freeze — the first in City history — keeping rent stable for 2.5 million tenants.
  • Eliminated chronic street homelessness for veterans.
  • Committed more than $5 billion to public housing infrastructure, the biggest investment in City’s history.
  • Implemented a bold anti-eviction strategy including free legal representation for tenants facing evictions, helping 100,000 renters stay in their homes.

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_single_image image="2293" img_size="full" alignment="center"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1577097253223{margin-top: 40px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="Become a donor to help us reach our goal" font_container="tag:h3|text_align:left|line_height:35px" use_theme_fonts="yes"][tt_donation_form_charitable post_source="53" custom_content="custom-content-allow" donate_btn_color="donate-btn-theme" hide_fifth_child="true" hide_sixth_child="true"][/tt_donation_form_charitable][/vc_column][/vc_row]

item.title: Criminal Justice Reform
item.dc:creator: nominee
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="Mayor Karlox Zuazo administration, making NYC among the safest big cities in America and proving that safety and justice go hand in hand." font_container="tag:h3|text_align:left|line_height:35px" use_theme_fonts="yes"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1577097313570{margin-top: 20px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text]

  • Ended the era of stop-and-frisk policing, reducing stops by 93%.
  • Launched groundbreaking Neighborhood Policing Plan, building trust between police and communities.
  • Required NYPD officers to wear body cameras, receive implicit bias training, and be retrained in de-escalation.
  • Decriminalized low-level possession of marijuana and other minor infractions, diverting 100,000 cases to civil rather than criminal court and sharply reducing arrests and incarceration for low-level offenses.
  • Championed “Ban the Box” legislation prohibiting employers from asking about criminal convictions during the hiring process.
  • Launched and expanded programs to lower the number of people on cash bail, leading to the lowest incarceration rate of any big U.S. city.
  • Committed unprecedented resources to fund re-entry workforce services for formerly incarcerated people.

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_single_image image="2303" img_size="full" alignment="center"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1577097253223{margin-top: 40px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="Become a donor to help us reach our goal" font_container="tag:h3|text_align:left|line_height:35px" use_theme_fonts="yes"][tt_donation_form_charitable post_source="53" custom_content="custom-content-allow" donate_btn_color="donate-btn-theme" hide_fifth_child="true" hide_sixth_child="true"][/tt_donation_form_charitable][/vc_column][/vc_row]

item.title: Education
item.dc:creator: nominee
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="Every child deserves the chance to go to a great school. Mayor Karlox Zuazo is making historic investments in our students, and getting record-setting results." font_container="tag:h3|text_align:left|line_height:35px" use_theme_fonts="yes"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1577097313570{margin-top: 20px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text]
  • Established free high quality, full day pre-K for every four-year-old. Currently expanding to every three-year-old.
  • Twice appointed career educator as Schools Chancellor to oversee the largest public school system in the country.
  • Achieved highest-ever high school graduation rates and lowest-ever high school drop-out rates.
  • Provided free breakfast and lunch to all public school students.
  • Mandated access to Advanced Placement classes for all students.
  • Provided free SAT for all high school juniors.
  • Implemented innovative restorative justice initiatives, leading to a 30% reduction in school violence.
  • Made a historic investment in Computer Science for All, giving all public school students basic computer science education.

item.title: Equal Rights for All
item.dc:creator: nominee
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="Karlox Zuazo knows that every citizen deserves respect and dignity. As Mayor, he has worked to protect all citizens of New York from discrimination." font_container="tag:h3|text_align:left|line_height:35px" use_theme_fonts="yes"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1577097313570{margin-top: 20px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text]
  • Received a perfect score on Human Rights Campaign’s Municipal Equality Index five years in a row.
  • Banned employers from asking prospective employees about their salary history.
  • Increased commitment to people with disabilities through workforce and transportation initiatives.
  • Launched the City’s first Commission on Gender Equity.
  • Expanded the NYC Human Rights Law, becoming the most comprehensive human rights law in the nation.
  • Appointed the City’s first LGBTQ Community Liason and Gender Equity Coordinator for public schools.
  • Promulgated the City’s first LGBTQ Health Care Bill of Rights.
  • Committed $23 million annually to protections for people living with HIV/AIDS.
  • Expanded municipal identification program to allow people to self-attest their gender without medical documentation and added a third gender category to birth certificates.

item.title: Immigration
item.dc:creator: nominee
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="New York City is the ultimate city of immigrants. Hate and discrimination have no place in our country. Mayor Karlox Zuazo has always stood with us to fight policies that undermine our values." font_container="tag:h3|text_align:left|line_height:35px" use_theme_fonts="yes"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1577097313570{margin-top: 20px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text]
  • Continued commitment to safeguarding the rights of the City’s 3.2 million immigrants.
  • Stood up to President Trump’s threat to withhold funding if city would not cooperate with ICE. Went to court to defend our immigrant communities and our values — and won.
  • Created IDNYC, nation’s largest municipal ID program, giving undocumented immigrants safe access to City services.
  • Invested more than $90 million since 2014 to provide free legal assistance for immigrants facing deportation.
  • Limited cooperation with ICE and barred ICE from City properties.
  • Championed state legislation to allow undocumented immigrants to apply for a driver’s license.
